'''William Lawther ("Will")''' (b. 20th May [[1889]], d. [[1976]]) was a [[British]] [[politician]] and [[trade union]] leader.

Lawther was President of the [[National Union of Mineworkers|Miners' Federation of Great Britain (MFGB)]]. He was the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] MP for the [[Barnard Castle (UK Parliament constituency)|Barnard Castle]] [[United Kingdom constituencies|constituency]] from 1929-1931.

